Natural state &ldquo;&ldquo;We as human-beings are inherently social creatures, and are used to operating within cooperative circles of extended family, groups/gangs, villages/tribes, etc.&rdquo;
&ldquo;Outside of family, research suggests there are only three levels of relationships: 1) Daily contact with 1-2 people (your significant other and maybe a best friend), 2) Weekly contact with 3-5 people (true friends that provide instrumental support), 3) Everyone else.&rdquo;
&ldquo;So what about the rest of your social network?
